title: Husker football game delayed because of Hurricane
text:
Husker football game delayed because of Hurricane Posted: 
8@klkntv.com 
Start Time Adjusted for Nebraska-Illinois Football Game 
Rosemont, Ill. – The impending weather impact of Hurricane Joaquin has adjusted a pair of start times for Big Ten games on Saturday.The Michigan at Maryland game in College Park has been moved from 7 p.m. (central) to 11 a.m. (central) on BTN, while Nebraska’s game with Illinois, which was scheduled to kick off at 2:42 p.m. (central), will now kick off at 3:02 p.m . The kickoff time was delayed 20 minutes to accommodate any potential weather-related delays in earlier games on Saturday. All content © Copyright 2000 - 2015 WorldNow and KLKN. All Rights Reserved.
